#### Summary

https://github.com/sebastianbergmann/phpunit/issues/6817 gets solved by https://github.com/sebastianbergmann/phpunit/commit/1d90b396fab98d85813d4127497ca6bd146f99ac but I forgot to mention that my error handler checks `error_reporting()` output dynamically

#### How to reproduce

`phpunit.xml`

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<phpunit xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../phpunit.xsd"
         cacheResult="false"
         bootstrap="bootstrap.php"
         displayDetailsOnAllIssues="true"
         failOnAllIssues="true"
>
</phpunit>
```

`bootstrap.php`

```php
<?php

final class MyErrorException extends \ErrorException {}

final class MyCustomException extends \Exception {}

error_reporting(E_ALL);
set_error_handler(static function ($level, $message, $file = null, $line = null): bool {
    if ($level & error_reporting()) {
        throw new MyErrorException($message, $level, $level, $file, $line);
    }

    return false;
});
```

`MyTest.php`

```php
<?php

final class MyTest extends \PHPUnit\Framework\TestCase
{
    public function testWarning(): void
    {
        $this->expectException(MyCustomException::class);

        try {
            trigger_error('warning from test', E_USER_WARNING);
        } catch (MyErrorException $e) {
            throw new MyCustomException('additional details', $e->getCode(), $e);
        }
    }
}
```

